---
3md: 1.0
category: Story
axis: frame
view: play
title: Forgetting
poet: Quill
note: A memory erodes one word at a time, falls silent, then rebuilds into the one image that stayed. Play it as a flipbook.
---
A poem that only works in motion. Each plane is one frame; play it and watch
the sentence lose a word at a time until nothing is left, then watch a smaller,
truer thing grow back in its place. The erasure is the poem.

@plane z=0 label="remember"


I remember all of it, that whole summer

@plane z=1 label="remember"


I remember all of it, that whole

@plane z=2 label="remember"


I remember all of it

@plane z=3 label="remember"


I remember all

@plane z=4 label="remember"


I remember

@plane z=5 label="remember"


I

@plane z=6 label="silence"


.

@plane z=7 label="return"


the

@plane z=8 label="return"


the light

@plane z=9 label="return"


the light, at least

@plane z=10 label="return"


the light, at least, stays
